Tsuga mortality revisited

  • Here using a subset of data from 2005, considering only Tsuga again (to keep our model simpler)
  • There are clear spatial patterns!
tsuga = readRDS("exercises/data/tsuga_spatial.rds")
pl1 = ggplot(tsuga, aes(x=X, y=Y, colour = died/n)) + geom_point() + coord_fixed() + 
    theme_minimal() + scico::scale_color_scico(palette="imola") + labs(color="pr(death)") + 
    ylab("Latitude (m)") + xlab("")
pl2 = ggplot(tsuga, aes(x=X, y=Y, colour = annual_mean_temp)) + geom_point() + coord_fixed() + 
    theme_minimal() + scico::scale_color_scico(palette="vik") + labs(color="temperature") + 
    ylab("Latitude (m)") + xlab("Longitude (m)")

Fitting the model

  • We compare 4 models
    • Spatial + temperature effect
    • Spatial only
    • Temperature only
    • Spatial + temperature + precipitation

Note: To run the code in this .rmd, you first need to run r/tsuga_fit.r, with your working directory set to docs.

models = readRDS("../scratch/gp_models.rds")
p1 = mcmc_trace(as.matrix(models[[1]], pars=c("a","b"))) + theme_minimal() + ggtitle("T")
p2 = mcmc_trace(as.matrix(models[[2]], pars=c("a","rho"))) + theme_minimal() + ggtitle("GP")
p3 = mcmc_trace(as.matrix(models[[3]], pars=c("a","rho"))) + theme_minimal() + ggtitle("GP+T")
p4 = mcmc_trace(as.matrix(models[[4]], pars=c("a","rho"))) + theme_minimal() + ggtitle("GP+T+P")
